scription>&lt;strong&gt;Mind vs. brain&lt;/strong&gt;: what are good introductory readings (high school) for the tendency to separate mind and brain. For example, one often hears statements like "the brain made me do it" etc. Of course the issues get thorny very quickly... &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111935951642686705</guid><pubDate>Thu, 15 Feb 2024 14:24:32 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/111935959593723386</link><description>If there is one thing we've learned in the 21st century, it is that cognition is not steady state.  It is dynamic and rhythmic.  Now, we seem to be reaching a tipping point of interest in traveling waves.  Stay tuned for our latest.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111935959662442701</guid><pubDate>Thu, 15 Feb 2024 14:26:35 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Marin Dacos - science ouverte</title><link>https://qoto.org/@marind/111936179654598019</link><description>French Ministry of Higher Education and Research partners with OpenAlex to develop a fully open bibliographic tool &lt;a href="https://www.ouvrirlascience.fr/french-ministry-of-higher-education-and-research-partners-with-openalex-to-develop-a-fully-open-bibliographic-tool/?utm_source=dlvr.it&amp;amp;utm_medium=mastodon" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;ouvrirlascience.fr/french-mini&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;stry-of-higher-education-and-research-partners-with-openalex-to-develop-a-fully-open-bibliographic-tool/?utm_source=dlvr.it&amp;amp;utm_medium=mastodon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111936526850652105</guid><pubDate>Thu, 15 Feb 2024 16:50:51 +0000</pubDate></item><item>